                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d703">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890G.6363/408: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-07T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 7, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 7—1:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. Legation’s telegram No. 140, April 7 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>], 3 p.m.
                    Necessary legislation has been passed by Parliament and Royal decree issued
                    ratifying IPC and Iraqi Government’s oil agreement as of May 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
